                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#20va">Fol. 20va</locus>: Purchase note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 20va: ዝሐዲሳት፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ መጥምቅ፡ ዘኰኮሎ፡ ዘተሣየጦ፡ ቄስ፡ ገበዝ፡ በኵረ፡ ጽዮን፡ በንዋየ፡ ዮሐንስ።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note states that the Ms. of the church Qǝddus Yoḥannǝs Mäṭmǝq of Kwäkolo was purchased during the gäbäz-tenure of priest Bäkwǝrä Ṣǝyon with the church's money. It is written in an angular script, some letters appear in a forked shape (ተ, ን, ዝ), probably in the same hand that re-wrote (partly) the ownership note on fol. 4ra (upper margin, s. "owner").
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#22r">Fol. 22r</locus>: Ownership note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 22r: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ጳውሎስ፡ ዘተስፋስላሴ፡ ወእሙ፡ ፍሬማርያም፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተሚካኤል፡ </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is crudely written in the upper margin. It states Täsfa Śǝllase as an owner of the "Book of Paul" and mentions also the names of his mother Fǝre Maryam and his wife Wälättä Mikaʾel. 
Similar notes in the same hand are written on fols. 62vb, 78rb, 98rab, 134rb (partly erased), 151ra (partly erased).
The same hand added the names of Täsfa Śǝllase (on fol. 29rb: Täsfa Sǝllasyä) and his wife on fols. 30vb, 35va, 48ra. In addition, the same scribe refers to the church of Kwäkwälo (fols. 52ra, 58ra) resp. of Däbrä Betel (fol. 82rb) as the owner.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Corrections are written over erasures: e.g., fols. 12vb, 22va, 62ra, 64rb, 69ra, 97rb, 102rb, 104ra, 143va; or interlineally, in a secondary hand: e.g., fols. 13rb, 87rb.&#xD;
- Commentaries are written in the margin or interlineally throughout Text XXIII in small script, in a secondary hand; occasionally some passages are crudely marked with lines.&#xD;
- Pen trial: fol. 3v.&#xD;
- Writing exercises (?) on the ruled endleaves appear upside down, in different hands: fols. 1v, 3r.&#xD;
- Erased notes: fol. 3r. &#xD;
- Crude minor notes and scribbles, in secondary recent hands: fols. 2r, 21rb, 151r-152v.</item>
                     </list>
